OL,3,CTUC calls for AI to be regulated in
OL,4,Cthe workplace
OL,6,F"Other countries are regulating
OL,7,Fworkplace AI ` so that staff and
OL,8,Femployers know where they stand. The
OL,9,FUK can't afford to drag its feet and
OL,10,Fbecome an international outlier."
OL,12,FA spokesperson for the Department for
OL,13,FScience, Innovation and Technology
OL,14,Fsaid: "Harnessing the power of AI
OL,15,Fshould not be at the expense of
OL,16,Femployment rights or protections ` and
OL,17,Fthat's why the UK is leading the world
OL,18,Fon the safe and responsible adoption
OL,19,Fof AI, having held the first ever AI
OL,20,FSummit at Bletchley Park last year.
